name: Bluetooth GNSS connector for OpenStreetMap Mappers
tagline: It support  Bluetooth GNSS(GPS, GLONASS, Galireo, Beidu, QZSS) reciever on Android for OpenStreetMap mappers.
body:
Bluetooth GPS/GNSS connector on Android for OpenStreetMap Mappers
===========

Description
-----

You can use an external GPS/GNSS reciever as same as internal one.
Connect external Bluetooth Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS)
receivers, using the GPS, GLONASS, Galileo, Beidou or QZSS system,
to your Android device.

Screenshots
----

![Main Screen](https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/90779460/2014_08_18_07.01.35.png)
![About](https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/90779460/2014_08_18_06.45.06.png)
![Settings](https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/90779460/2014_08_18_06.44.30.png)
![Rador](https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/90779460/2014_08_17_15.13.25.png)

Rador Interface: Each satellites have prefix in name; 

- G: GPS
- R: GLONASS
- E: Galileo
- S: SBS(WAAS, MSAS, EGNOS, etc)
- B: Beidou/Compass
- Q: QZSS
